1. Patients diagnosed with a major depressive episode were part of the study.
2. The patients were randomized for the study.
3. The intervention lasted for 11 weeks.
4. The intervention included 1 week of CBM-I and 10 weeks of iCBT.
5. The intervention was delivered via the Internet.
6. There was no face-to-face patient contact in the intervention.
7. The number of patients in the intervention group was 38.
8. There was a wait-list control group in the study.
9. The number of patients in the wait-list control group was 31.

messages.content:
